comments: Powell (DAL) places a hand/arm to the front of George (OKC) during the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Westbrook (OKC) dislodges Brunson (DAL) during the loose ball.
Broekhoff (DAL) holds Adams' (OKC) arm and affects his ability to move freely as he rolls towards the rim.
Burke (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
George (OKC) moves along Burke's (DAL) path and absorbs the oncoming body contact during the driving shot attempt.
Powell (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Westbrook (OKC) and delivers some contact but does not affect his ability to defend.
Grant (OKC) makes marginal contact with Powell's (DAL) arm as he also dislodges the ball out of bounds.
Kleber (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position during George's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
Broekhoff (DAL) makes marginal contact to George's (OKC) body during the drive.
George (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Brunson (DAL) and does not deliver contact during the screen.
Burke (DAL) slightly follows-through with his arm to Grant's (OKC) body, but doesn't affect his shot attempt near the rim.
LAR shows that Kleber (DAL) moves along Westbrook's (OKC) path and absorbs the body contact at the end of the drive. Although Kleber (DAL) slightly extends his arm, the contact is marginal.
George (OKC) briefly engages with Kleber (DAL) off ball and separates from him without affecting his ability to move freely.
Burke (DAL) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Schroder (OKC) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Adams (OKC) briefly engages with Kleber (DAL), but doesn't affect his ability to get through the screen.
Schroder (OKC) commits a take foul on Broekhoff (DAL).
